'''Batokunku''' (also spelled ''Batukunku'') is a village located in [[Kombo South]], one of the nine districts of [[The Gambia]]'s [[Western Division (The Gambia)|Western Division]]. In January 2009, the village became notable as the location of the first [[wind turbine]] erected in West Africa. The 150 kilowatt turbine, a second-hand machine originally built by the [[Denmark|Danish]] wind energy manufacturer Bonus, currently provides electrical power for the entire village.<ref>{{cite news | author =Dierk Jensen | title =A Second Life in Africa | publisher =New Energy Magazine | date =March 2009 }}</ref> The windmill is currently serviced/maintained by Global Energy (generator service) based in the nearby village of Tujereng in collaboration with Windstrom SH from Germany.
